# Release Documentation Checklist

When promoting an RC to stable or shipping a new release, update **all** of these before the final commit:

## Documentation touchpoints

1. **Root `README.md`**
   - Features table (tab descriptions, new capabilities)
   - CAN table / OBD polling table (new signals, changed formulas)
   - Architecture diagram (header layout, new components)
   - Settings table (new user-facing options)
   - Contributing section (remove verified items from wishlist)
   - Roadmap (move completed items, update planned phases)
   - Project structure tree (new files, renamed files)

2. **`firmware/README.md`**
   - Version string at top ("Current versions: ...")
   - Hardware compatibility table (status changes, e.g. experimental to verified)
   - Build output table (binary filenames must match current versions)
   - Release directory listing (binary filenames)
   - Drive mode / ESC / CAN frame docs (timing, bit positions, behavior changes)
   - REST API examples (version in response)
   - Directory structure (new source files)
   - Roadmap section (next priorities)

3. **`android/README.md`**
   - Project structure tree (new files)

4. **`android/docs/pid-reference.md`**
   - New PIDs, changed formulas, confirmed/unconfirmed status updates
   - Architecture notes for new polling approaches

5. **GitHub issues**
   - Close any issues resolved by the release, with a comment citing the release version
   - Check for superseded issues that should be closed as duplicates

## Binary filenames

When a firmware version changes, the binary filename must match. Update `OUTPUT_BIN` in `build.sh` and `git rm` the old filename. See `firmware-versioning.mdc` for the full checklist.

6. **Browser emulator** (`android/browser-emulator/index.html`)
   - Must mirror every visible app change (see `release-checklist.mdc` section 3 for full details)
   - Version badge, new/removed widgets, tab changes, data labels, feature cards, demo data
   - This is the public-facing demo -- it must match the shipped app

## Don't forget

- Stale "experimental" / "pending hardware test" / "unverified" labels in docs
- Roadmap items that are now complete
- Contributing wishlist items that are now resolved
- File trees that reference old filenames
- Browser emulator parity with app UI
